#: src/ui/tray.md:3
msgid ""
"Perry ships a cross-platform system tray API on `perry/ui` (issue #490). The"
" same six functions work on every desktop target â macOS, Windows, "
"Linux/GTK4 â and link as no-ops on the mobile / embedded backends."
msgstr ""
"Perry embarque une API de barre d'ÃĐtat systÃĻme (system tray) multiplateforme"
" sur `perry/ui` (issue #490). Les six mÃŠmes fonctions fonctionnent sur "
"chaque cible bureau â macOS, Windows, Linux/GTK4 â et sont liÃĐes comme des "
"no-ops sur les backends mobiles / embarquÃĐs."

#: src/ui/tray.md:7
msgid ""
"The API is **handle-based** and free-function: build a tray with "
"`trayCreate(iconPath)`, attach a context menu built with the existing "
"`menuCreate` / `menuAddItem` API via `trayAttachMenu(tray, menu)`, and "
"register a left-click callback with `trayOnClick`."
msgstr ""
"L'API est **basÃĐe sur des handles** et sous forme de fonctions libres : "
"crÃĐez une icÃīne de barre d'ÃĐtat avec `trayCreate(iconPath)`, attachez un "
"menu contextuel construit avec l'API existante `menuCreate` / `menuAddItem` "
"via `trayAttachMenu(tray, menu)`, et enregistrez un callback de clic gauche "
"avec `trayOnClick`."

#: src/ui/tray.md:14
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// Build the tray BEFORE App() â the tray icon installs while the\n"
"// runtime is starting up, so it's already live when the main window\n"
"// appears.\n"
"const tray = trayCreate(\"\")  // empty path â \"â\" placeholder\n"
"traySetTooltip(tray, \"My App\")\n"
"\n"
"// Right-click (or left-click on macOS) opens the menu attached below.\n"
"const menu = menuCreate()\n"
"menuAddItem(menu, \"Show\", () => status.set(\"tray/show\"))\n"
"menuAddSeparator(menu)\n"
"menuAddItem(menu, \"Quit\", () => status.set(\"tray/quit\"))\n"
"trayAttachMenu(tray, menu)\n"
"\n"
"// Optional: left-click handler. On macOS the menu pops on left-click,\n"
"// so this fires only when no menu is attached. On Windows / Linux,\n"
"// left-click and the menu are independent â typical usage is\n"
"// \"left-click â show main window, right-click â menu\".\n"
"trayOnClick(tray, () => {\n"
"    status.set(\"tray/click\")\n"
"})\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

