#: src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:88
msgid ""
"`PERRY_ALLOW_PERRY_FEATURES=1` opts every package into both allowlists for "
"the current build â emergency knob for one-off builds where editing "
"`package.json` isn't an option. `=0` enforces refusal even when "
"`package.json` opted in (fail-closed CI gate)."
msgstr ""
"`PERRY_ALLOW_PERRY_FEATURES=1` autorise tous les packages dans les deux "
"listes d'autorisation pour la build en cours â commande d'urgence pour les "
"builds ponctuelles oÃđ la modification de `package.json` n'est pas possible. "
"`=0` impose le refus mÃŠme si `package.json` a optÃĐ (verrou CI fail-closed)."

#: src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:93
msgid "Default-deny rationale"
msgstr "Raison du refus par dÃĐfaut"

#: src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:95
msgid "Both features escape Perry's structural guarantees:"
msgstr ""
"Les deux fonctionnalitÃĐs contournent les garanties structurelles de Perry :"

#: src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:97
msgid ""
"`nativeLibrary` lets a transitive dep ship arbitrary machine code that runs "
"at the same trust level as the host application."
msgstr ""
"`nativeLibrary` permet Ã  une dÃĐpendance transitive de livrer du code machine"
" arbitraire s'exÃĐcutant au mÃŠme niveau de confiance que l'application hÃīte."

#: src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:99
msgid ""
"`compilePackages` runs the dep's TypeScript through Perry's full native "
"pipeline (HIR / codegen / linker) instead of routing it through QuickJS, "
"eliminating the runtime sandbox."
msgstr ""
"`compilePackages` fait passer le TypeScript de la dÃĐpendance par le pipeline"
" natif complet de Perry (HIR / codegen / linker) au lieu de le router via "
"QuickJS, supprimant ainsi le sandbox d'exÃĐcution."

#: src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:103
msgid ""
"Both are useful features, but they're _privileged_ operations. The allowlist"
" makes that privilege explicit and auditable: a reviewer diffing a PR can "
"see exactly which deps have been granted native access, and `git blame` "
"records who approved each one."
msgstr ""
"Ces deux fonctionnalitÃĐs sont utiles, mais il s'agit d'opÃĐrations "
"_privilÃĐgiÃĐes_. La liste d'autorisation rend ce privilÃĻge explicite et "
"auditable : un relecteur qui examine une PR peut voir exactement quelles "
"dÃĐpendances ont reÃ§u un accÃĻs natif, et `git blame` enregistre qui a "
"approuvÃĐ chacune d'elles."

#: src/cli/allow-perry-features.md:110
msgid ""
"[`#497`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/497) â design discussion."
msgstr ""
"[`#497`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/497) â discussion de "
"conception."

